<i>Si si.</i>

261
00:31:49,052 --> 00:31:51,096
Say something.

262
00:31:51,221 --> 00:31:52,931
Say something more.

263
00:31:55,100 --> 00:31:56,643
No.

264
00:31:56,768 --> 00:31:58,561
Oh, talk to me.

265
00:31:58,687 --> 00:32:01,147
Talk. Talk.

266
00:32:13,118 --> 00:32:15,036
<i>[ Baby Crying]</i>

267
00:33:51,674 --> 00:33:53,760
<i>[ Crying Continues]</i>

268
00:34:21,955 --> 00:34:24,499
<i>[ Men Speaking Sicilian]</i>

269
00:34:45,979 --> 00:34:48,314
[ Italian ]

270
00:34:51,484 --> 00:34:53,194
Who are you?

271
00:34:53,319 --> 00:34:55,321
Those people work in America.

272
00:34:55,446 --> 00:34:59,033
America
is a big country, beautiful.

273
00:34:59,158 --> 00:35:02,453
Your husband sent us
to work in this house.

274
00:35:02,579 --> 00:35:04,873
Lots of people was in New York.

275
00:35:04,998 --> 00:35:07,125
I had a son in America...

276
00:35:07,292 --> 00:35:10,128
and I was working -
[ Broken English ]

277
00:35:10,253 --> 00:35:13,089
And I make good money too.

278
00:35:13,214 --> 00:35:17,802
On Sunday
I even go fish in automobile.

279
00:35:17,969 --> 00:35:20,096
I even go in automobile...

280
00:35:20,221 --> 00:35:22,557
to get my relief check.

281
00:35:22,682 --> 00:35:25,894
Everybody in America
drive automobile.

282
00:35:26,019 --> 00:35:27,896
We come all to Stromboli.

283
00:35:28,021 --> 00:35:30,023
<i>You see that hole?</i>

284
00:35:30,148 --> 00:35:33,776
<i>Volcano is very dangerous.
Sometime blow up...</i>

285
00:35:33,902 --> 00:35:37,238
and lots stones go up
and come down...

286
00:35:37,363 --> 00:35:39,282
break the floor
and make big hole...

287
00:35:39,407 --> 00:35:42,493
and burn everything,
like in 1944.

288
00:35:42,619 --> 00:35:44,037
<i>Why did you leave America?</i>

289
00:35:44,162 --> 00:35:47,123
I leave America -
America is good for young fellows.

290
00:35:47,248 --> 00:35:50,668
<i>I am old man,
and I come back to Stromboli.</i>

291
00:35:50,835 --> 00:35:53,087
This fellow too old...

292
00:35:53,212 --> 00:35:55,256
and stupid in the head.

293
00:35:55,381 --> 00:35:57,008
I don't want to die here.

294
00:35:57,175 --> 00:36:00,053
I want to go back over
to my son in Brooklyn...

295
00:36:00,178 --> 00:36:02,931
and he saves money for my trip.

296
00:36:03,056 --> 00:36:07,018
I am going back in Brooklyn
in about 10 years.

297
00:36:07,185 --> 00:36:09,187
- How old are you?
- Seventy-three.

298
00:36:24,243 --> 00:36:26,996
<i>[ Chi/d</i> Shouting]
Signora! Signora!

299
00:36:33,211 --> 00:36:36,089
[Shouting In Italian ]

300
00:36:43,054 --> 00:36:44,931
Good morning.
How are you today?

301
00:36:45,056 --> 00:36:47,767
Good morning, Father.

302
00:36:47,892 --> 00:36:50,186
I was wondering
how you're getting along.

303
00:36:50,311 --> 00:36:52,438
You can see for yourself.
I stay out here.

304
00:36:52,563 --> 00:36:56,109
My house is filled with little old men
who speak about America all the time.

305
00:36:56,234 --> 00:36:58,152
- Sit down.
- Thank you.

306
00:36:58,277 --> 00:37:02,156
Well, with a little time and patience,
everything will be all right.

307
00:37:02,281 --> 00:37:05,493
Everything? You mean this island
and the volcano too?

308
00:37:05,618 --> 00:37:08,579
No. I mean
your home and you.

309
00:37:08,705 --> 00:37:11,082
Maybe I can help you.

310
00:37:11,249 --> 00:37:15,503
I told your husband it was all right
to take the tiles from the Moletta house.

311
00:37:15,628 --> 00:37:18,881
The Molettas left this island
26 years ago.

312
00:37:19,007 --> 00:37:21,384
I don't think they'll mind.
You see...

313
00:37:21,509 --> 00:37:24,137
I'm sort of a trustee
for the properties...

314
00:37:24,262 --> 00:37:26,264
of those who have gone abroad.

315
00:37:29,392 --> 00:37:32,270
I think the tiles will make
your room a little brighter...

316
00:37:32,395 --> 00:37:34,397
and nobody will mind
a little robbery.

317
00:37:36,232 --> 00:37:40,194
<i>Those who have gone away
help those who are left behind.</i>

318
00:37:40,319 --> 00:37:43,698
<i>And I, well,
I act as the middleman.</i>

319
00:37:43,823 --> 00:37:46,242
Then try to help us, Father.

320
00:37:46,367 --> 00:37:48,828
I can't take life like this.

321
00:37:48,953 --> 00:37:52,081
Antonio is still a boy.
Yes, I love him...

322
00:37:52,206 --> 00:37:54,792
but he doesn't understand
how a woman like me feels.

323
00:37:54,917 --> 00:37:56,711
I think he does.

324
00:37:58,379 --> 00:38:01,007
I know how hard
he try to get work.

325
00:38:01,132 --> 00:38:03,009
The fishing season
has started...

326
00:38:03,134 --> 00:38:05,720
and the boats have
full crews already.

327
00:38:05,845 --> 00:38:08,806
You see, there are only
four boats from Stromboli.

328
00:38:08,973 --> 00:38:11,642
The rest come
from other islands.

329
00:38:11,809 --> 00:38:16,105
Yet Antonio has managed
to find a place.

330
00:38:16,230 --> 00:38:18,816
He sacrificed his pride.

331
00:38:18,941 --> 00:38:21,402
He owned a boat of his own
once, you know.

332
00:38:21,527 --> 00:38:25,156
He has done it all for you.
I know it because I talked with him.

333
00:38:25,323 --> 00:38:29,202
Yes, I suppose he's doing his best,
but can't he realize that -

334
00:38:29,327 --> 00:38:32,997
that I can't live here
and that he should take me away?

335
00:38:33,122 --> 00:38:36,501
You need money to emigrate,
and a place to go.

336
00:38:38,002 --> 00:38:41,506
Those who were born here -
all they wanted was to leave.

337
00:38:41,631 --> 00:38:44,258
You can imagine how I feel,
Father, a stranger.

338
00:38:44,383 --> 00:38:46,844
These black rocks,
this desolation...

339
00:38:47,011 --> 00:38:48,888
that - that terror.

340
00:38:50,431 --> 00:38:53,643
This island drives me mad, Father.
Won't you help us, please?

341
00:38:53,768 --> 00:38:55,311
You are both young.

342
00:38:55,436 --> 00:38:57,814
Make Antonio save his money
instead of spending it.

343
00:38:57,939 --> 00:39:01,609
Help him, and perhaps you will
be able to leave too someday.

344
00:39:01,734 --> 00:39:03,861
But while you have
to stay here...

345
00:39:04,028 --> 00:39:07,073
make a good home
for yourself and for him.

346
00:39:07,198 --> 00:39:10,451
It will make it easier
for both of you to wait.

347
00:39:10,576 --> 00:39:12,745
If you do this,
merciful God will help you.

348
00:39:12,870 --> 00:39:15,039
With me, God has
never been merciful.

349
00:41:50,653 --> 00:41:52,488
Karin!

350
00:41:52,613 --> 00:41:55,825
<i>Guarda.</i> Look.
[ Sicilian ]

351
00:41:55,950 --> 00:41:59,912
I caught many, many fish.
[Sicilian ] We are rich!

352
00:42:00,037 --> 00:42:02,206
I'm going to Messina
to sell all the fish.

353
00:42:02,331 --> 00:42:04,292
What fish?
What are you talking about?

354
00:42:04,417 --> 00:42:07,586
Like this, you see?
Many, many. Fantastic.

355
00:42:07,712 --> 00:42:09,714
[Sicilian ]

356
00:42:11,465 --> 00:42:13,384
[Sicilian ]

357
00:42:15,261 --> 00:42:17,138
We sell the fish.

358
00:42:19,223 --> 00:42:20,975
We sell the fish.

359
00:42:22,768 --> 00:42:24,353
<i>Ciao.</i>

360
00:42:25,271 --> 00:42:27,231
<i>[ Footsteps Retreating]</i>

361
00:44:52,626 --> 00:44:54,712
<i>" [ Man ] Signora!
Yes'?"</i>

362
00:44:58,716 --> 00:45:01,635
<i>All finished.
You want to see?</i>

363
00:45:01,760 --> 00:45:03,554
Yes, I'm coming.

364
00:45:10,603 --> 00:45:13,063
<i>- How do you</i> like?
- <i>O bra v/I/ Be/I/s/mo/</i>

365
00:45:17,985 --> 00:45:20,196
- [ Laughs]
- How do you like it?

366
00:45:20,321 --> 00:45:22,656
It's wonderful.
Just wonderful.

367
00:45:22,781 --> 00:45:25,034
Thank you.
Thank you very much.

368
00:45:28,746 --> 00:45:31,081
Did you finish
painting that bench?

369
00:45:31,248 --> 00:45:33,584
I want it in here right away.

370
00:45:33,751 --> 00:45:35,753
I cut the chair.
Is it all right?

371
00:45:35,878 --> 00:45:38,756
No, you haven't.
I want you to cut the legs off.

372
00:45:38,923 --> 00:45:41,467
I did cut them.
But you want them shorter?

373
00:45:41,592 --> 00:45:43,761
Yes, but I want them
like the other chairs.

374
00:45:43,886 --> 00:45:47,681
- I want all the chairs real low, you see?
- Yes. All right.

375
00:45:47,806 --> 00:45:49,517
Thank you.

376
00:46:07,117 --> 00:46:09,078
N' [ Humming ]

377
00:46:33,185 --> 00:46:35,104
Good morning.

378
00:46:35,229 --> 00:46:38,899
Would you like to come in
and see the house?

379
00:46:39,024 --> 00:46:42,820
Il/lo/to gentile of you
to come and see me.

380
00:46:46,657 --> 00:46:48,659
I'd like you to come in
and see the house.

381
00:46:48,826 --> 00:46:50,494
En-Enter.

382
00:46:50,661 --> 00:46:52,538
<i>Entrate.</i>

383
00:46:52,663 --> 00:46:56,250
Please, translate for them.
Tell them I would like them to come in.

384
00:46:56,375 --> 00:46:58,794
[Sicilian ]

385
00:47:06,510 --> 00:47:08,304
- Did you tell them?
- Yes.

386
00:47:08,429 --> 00:47:11,181
- What did they say?
- You heard: just nothing.

387
00:47:11,348 --> 00:47:14,643
Good morning, Rosaria. Would you
like to come in and see the house?

388
00:47:14,768 --> 00:47:17,271
- No.
- But what is the matter?

389
00:47:17,396 --> 00:47:21,066
Why are you all against me? I haven't hurt anyone.
Why does everyone act like this?

390
00:47:21,191 --> 00:47:24,653
Why you do things like this?
You are not modest.

391
00:47:26,697 --> 00:47:29,617
But I haven't done
anything wrong.

392
00:47:29,742 --> 00:47:31,827
It's not my fault
if I'm different.

393
00:47:31,952 --> 00:47:34,538
I look different,
I act different, and I feel different.

394
00:47:34,705 --> 00:47:36,986
I've tried to make the house
better for me and my husband.

395
00:47:37,082 --> 00:47:39,043
What in the world
can you have against that?

396
00:47:39,209 --> 00:47:40,878
You have no modesty.

397
00:47:59,980 --> 00:48:01,899
The weather's clearing up, huh?

398
00:48:02,066 --> 00:48:04,193
Too much wind
on the other side of the island.

399
00:48:04,318 --> 00:48:06,445
You don't think my husband
will come home tonight?

400
00:48:06,570 --> 00:48:09,239
No, don't think so.

401
00:48:09,365 --> 00:48:12,993
Then do me a favor and take me to the
woman who has the sewing machine.

402
00:48:13,118 --> 00:48:15,120
The one who fixed
the curtains for me.

403
00:48:15,245 --> 00:48:17,498
I'd like her to help me
with my new dress.

404
00:48:17,623 --> 00:48:20,250
It will be easier to wait
if I have something to do.

405
00:48:20,417 --> 00:48:24,588
That woman is not so good.
Her reputation is cosi cosi.

406
00:48:24,755 --> 00:48:27,341
I don't care if her reputation
is <i>cosi</i> cosi.

407
00:48:27,466 --> 00:48:30,427
I'm old enough to take care of myself.
How far is she?

408
00:48:30,594 --> 00:48:32,429
- On the other side of the church.
- Wait.

409
00:48:32,596 --> 00:48:36,058
I'll get the material,
and then you can take me there.

410
00:48:57,621 --> 00:48:59,456
Why did she do that to me?

411
00:48:59,623 --> 00:49:01,625
Maybe not on purpose.

412
00:49:15,973 --> 00:49:17,683
This is the house.

413
00:49:17,808 --> 00:49:19,810
This is the -
Does she speak English?

414
00:49:19,935 --> 00:49:21,895
- No.
- Will you come in and help me?

415
00:49:22,020 --> 00:49:23,397
- No.
- Why not?

416
00:49:23,522 --> 00:49:25,649
Because my wife
is very jealous.

417
00:49:25,774 --> 00:49:29,111
Oh. [Laughing]
All right. Good night. Thank you.

418
00:49:29,236 --> 00:49:30,779
<i>Bye.</i>

419
00:49:33,991 --> 00:49:35,659
<i>[ Sheep Bleating]</i>

420
00:49:39,496 --> 00:49:41,165
[ Knocking ]

421
00:49:42,583 --> 00:49:45,419
- <i>Buona sera.</i>
- <i>Buona sera.</i>

422
00:49:45,544 --> 00:49:49,882
<i>Could you cue/re for me
on the macch/ha?</i>

423
00:49:50,007 --> 00:49:51,675
<i>Si.</i>

424
00:50:00,851 --> 00:50:02,352
<i>Cosi.</i>

425
00:50:04,605 --> 00:50:06,190
<i>Si.</i>

426
00:50:06,315 --> 00:50:07,900
There.

427
00:50:12,696 --> 00:50:14,615
<i>[ Treadle Whirring]</i>

428
00:50:19,620 --> 00:50:21,497
Oh, it's you.

429
00:50:23,040 --> 00:50:25,793
- What's the matter? Are you sick?
- No, just malaria.

430
00:50:25,918 --> 00:50:27,878
Oh, malaria.

431
00:50:28,045 --> 00:50:30,380
What's going to happen
to your lighthouse when you're gone?

432
00:50:30,547 --> 00:50:31,924
<i>[Man ] My mate is there.</i>

433
00:50:32,049 --> 00:50:36,094
Poor fellow. He has to stay on that rock
all alone until you get well?

434
00:50:36,220 --> 00:50:37,679
<i>Si si.</i>

435
00:50:45,479 --> 00:50:48,065
<i>' S/Qﬂora?</i>
'Hmm?

436
00:50:48,190 --> 00:50:49,775
<i>Grazie.</i>

437
00:51:03,997 --> 00:51:06,291
[Sicilian ]

438
00:51:06,416 --> 00:51:08,836
Fine, thank you.
I can try it on.

439
00:51:08,961 --> 00:51:11,505
Oh, it's already dark.

440
00:51:29,857 --> 00:51:32,693
<i>JV' [ Men Singing In Sicilian ]</i>

441
00:51:32,818 --> 00:51:34,820
<i>♪! [ Guitar]</i>

442
00:52:06,059 --> 00:52:07,519
[Sicilian ]

443
00:52:07,644 --> 00:52:09,771
[Sicilian ]

444
00:52:09,897 --> 00:52:12,024
<i>[ Men Chuckling]</i>

445
00:52:12,149 --> 00:52:13,984
<i>JV' [ Resumes]</i>

446
00:52:22,492 --> 00:52:24,453
[Sicilian ]

447
00:52:33,503 --> 00:52:35,505
N' [ Resumes ]

448
00:52:46,099 --> 00:52:48,352
- Karin!
- You came back.

449
00:52:48,477 --> 00:52:50,479
- Let's get out of here.
- Let me change.

450
00:52:50,604 --> 00:52:53,315
- You don't want to make me look ridiculous
- - We're going now!

451
00:53:24,054 --> 00:53:25,931
<i>JV' [ Resumes]</i>

452
00:53:27,391 --> 00:53:29,017
Come on.

453
00:53:31,436 --> 00:53:33,105
<i>Cammina.</i>

454
00:53:35,023 --> 00:53:37,442
[ Sicilian ] I break your face!

455
00:53:37,567 --> 00:53:39,569
What's the matter?
I haven't done anything wrong.

456
00:53:39,736 --> 00:53:41,697
I went there to use
her sewing machine.

457
00:53:41,822 --> 00:53:43,740
You went to the house
of a bad woman.

458
00:53:46,868 --> 00:53:49,955
- I'll show you.
- Yes, yes, you'll show me. But you don't scare me!

459
00:53:50,080 --> 00:53:51,123
<i>Cammina.</i>

460
00:54:05,095 --> 00:54:07,222
<i>JV' [ Continues ]</i>

461
00:54:23,989 --> 00:54:25,991
The money went to your head.

462
00:54:27,784 --> 00:54:29,995
I suppose you came back rich...

463
00:54:30,120 --> 00:54:31,830
and that's why
you're acting this way.

464
00:54:33,749 --> 00:54:36,668
Well, how much did you get
selling your fish?

465
00:54:36,793 --> 00:54:38,587
Here. This.

466
00:54:42,507 --> 00:54:44,342
How much is it?

467
00:54:44,468 --> 00:54:47,846
<i>30,000 lire. About $40.</i>

468
00:54:47,971 --> 00:54:49,723
30,000 lire.

469
00:54:49,848 --> 00:54:52,976
- My partners got more money than me.
- Why?

470
00:54:53,143 --> 00:54:56,938
They took advantage of me
because you are different.

471
00:54:57,064 --> 00:55:00,108
They know I have
to take care of you.

472
00:55:00,233 --> 00:55:02,319
They know
I cannot wait for better job.

473
00:55:02,444 --> 00:55:04,988
<i>They give me a smaller share...</i>

474
00:55:05,113 --> 00:55:06,907
<i>that I will work more for you.</i>

475
00:55:14,289 --> 00:55:16,333
I will work more for you.

476
00:55:20,378 --> 00:55:22,255
Don't worry about it.

477
00:55:23,340 --> 00:55:25,634
- Give me a match.
- Yes.

478
00:55:35,560 --> 00:55:37,145
So-

479
00:55:40,774 --> 00:55:43,193
- You change everything.
- Mm-hmm.

480
00:55:43,360 --> 00:55:44,945
Pictures.

481
00:55:45,070 --> 00:55:47,989
Yes, the pictures of your family,
I put them away.

482
00:55:48,115 --> 00:55:50,534
- Madonna?
- The Madonna too.

483
00:55:50,700 --> 00:55:53,995
- My mama put the Madonna there.
- All right.

484
00:55:54,121 --> 00:55:56,581
I didn't throw it away.
I just moved it.

485
00:55:56,706 --> 00:55:58,208
Look here.

486
00:55:59,709 --> 00:56:03,171
A tree... in the house.

487
00:56:03,296 --> 00:56:05,340
Yes. You don't like it?

488
00:56:06,508 --> 00:56:08,135
Yes.

489
00:56:08,260 --> 00:56:09,845
Maybe.

490
00:56:13,056 --> 00:56:15,767
I did as you suggested.

491
00:56:15,892 --> 00:56:20,272
I changed the house
to make it better for him, for me.

492
00:56:20,397 --> 00:56:22,816
To make the waiting easier.

493
00:56:24,151 --> 00:56:26,069
But when he saw it...

494
00:56:26,194 --> 00:56:27,821
it bothered him.

495
00:56:29,990 --> 00:56:32,826
He didn't have the courage
to say anything, but I -

496
00:56:32,951 --> 00:56:34,828
I knew he was hurt...

497
00:56:34,953 --> 00:56:37,122
and this morning
he went through...

498
00:56:37,247 --> 00:56:40,667
all the old things
that I'd put away -

499
00:56:40,792 --> 00:56:44,379
the awful furniture,
pictures, holy images -

500
00:56:44,504 --> 00:56:48,550
and when he held them in his hand,
I could feel his great nostalgia...

501
00:56:48,675 --> 00:56:51,636
and his resentment towards me.

502
00:56:51,761 --> 00:56:53,555
I understand him.

503
00:56:53,680 --> 00:56:57,267
Antonio is a good, simple boy.

504
00:56:57,392 --> 00:57:01,938
In all his life, his only experience
has been his military service.

505
00:57:02,063 --> 00:57:04,024
Yes, I understand him too,
Father...

506
00:57:04,149 --> 00:57:06,735
but who understands me?

507
00:57:06,860 --> 00:57:08,862
You are the only man here...

508
00:57:08,987 --> 00:57:11,948
who can understand, perhaps.

509
00:57:12,073 --> 00:57:15,452
Please advise me and help me.
I - I'm going mad.

510
00:57:15,577 --> 00:57:18,288
I'm so unhappy, Father.

511
00:57:18,413 --> 00:57:21,124
I suffer, believe me.

512
00:57:21,249 --> 00:57:23,710
You must have courage.

513
00:57:23,835 --> 00:57:25,795
I told you:
You're both young.

514
00:57:25,921 --> 00:57:30,217
Must I waste my youth here?
It's inhuman. I can't go on.

515
00:57:30,342 --> 00:57:32,552
What is it you want to do?

516
00:57:32,677 --> 00:57:34,971
<i>I -</i> I don't know.

517
00:57:35,138 --> 00:57:38,475
You must try to find a way,
Father, to help me.

518
00:57:38,642 --> 00:57:40,477
Help me.

519
00:57:40,644 --> 00:57:43,980
Antonio - you know
how poor his English is.

520
00:57:44,147 --> 00:57:46,149
If I don't speak to him
like a child...

521
00:57:46,274 --> 00:57:48,068
he doesn't understand.

522
00:57:48,193 --> 00:57:49,986
One word is enough
to upset him.

523
00:57:50,153 --> 00:57:52,239
Will you explain
to him, Father?

524
00:57:52,364 --> 00:57:54,282
He doesn't need explanation.

525
00:57:54,407 --> 00:57:56,743
The boy is just as unhappy
as you are.

526
00:57:56,868 --> 00:57:58,536
Maybe even more.

527
00:57:58,662 --> 00:58:00,997
<i>Then there is no way out?
No hope?</i>

528
00:58:01,122 --> 00:58:03,041
Be patient and calm.

529
00:58:03,166 --> 00:58:07,128
Perhaps I can write to some
of our people in America or Australia...

530
00:58:07,254 --> 00:58:10,715
and see if there is a way
they can bring you there.

531
00:58:10,840 --> 00:58:13,218
Please, please do.
Do you think it is possible?

532
00:58:13,343 --> 00:58:17,305
I think so. The people
who were born on this island...

533
00:58:17,430 --> 00:58:19,224
are very good people-

534
00:58:19,349 --> 00:58:23,186
Take, for instance, Francesco Dimattina,
who went to America.

535
00:58:23,311 --> 00:58:27,190
He died lately,
a widower without children...

536
00:58:27,357 --> 00:58:30,485
and left $3,000,
all his fortune...

537
00:58:30,610 --> 00:58:32,529
to Stromboli...

538
00:58:32,696 --> 00:58:35,532
for the old
and to keep up the cemetery.

539
00:58:35,657 --> 00:58:38,868
He left the money in my care.

540
00:58:38,994 --> 00:58:42,622
I knew right away that you would be
the only one who could help us.

541
00:58:42,747 --> 00:58:47,085
I'm only a poor churchman,
but I understand human suffering.

542
00:58:47,210 --> 00:58:50,714
The dead find their peace
in desolate cemeteries...

543
00:58:50,839 --> 00:58:53,883
swept by the wind and burned
by the sun, while we the living -

544
00:58:54,050 --> 00:58:57,450
- I know. I know.
- Don't you think the memory of your friend would be more honored...

545
00:58:57,554 --> 00:59:01,057
if you gave the money
to two young people who want to live?

546
00:59:01,224 --> 00:59:04,185
- Perhaps, but I can't -
- Please listen to me. You -

547
00:59:04,311 --> 00:59:07,772
You don't know about me,
and you don't know my past.

548
00:59:07,897 --> 00:59:09,774
I g

549
00:59:09,899 --> 00:59:12,861
I have been lost.
I have sinned.

550
00:59:12,986 --> 00:59:15,488
I have chased
after illusions, adventure...

551
00:59:16,573 --> 00:59:19,909
as if an evil force
were in back of me.

552
00:59:20,035 --> 00:59:22,454
Now I realize
how wrong I've been...

553
00:59:22,579 --> 00:59:24,998
and I want to make
something out of my life...

554
00:59:25,123 --> 00:59:26,958
but this is too much.

555
00:59:27,083 --> 00:59:31,338
You-You can't go
from one extreme to another.

556
00:59:31,463 --> 00:59:33,214
<i>[Sobbing ]</i>

557
00:59:33,340 --> 00:59:35,300
I've known this all along.

558
00:59:35,425 --> 00:59:39,763
I sympathized with you
from the day you came to the island.

559
00:59:39,888 --> 00:59:43,683
That's why I tried to give you
whatever spiritual help I could.

560
00:59:46,227 --> 00:59:48,355
Oh, you're a good man.

561
00:59:54,778 --> 00:59:56,488
<i>Grazie.</i>

562
00:59:59,491 --> 01:00:01,451
This will calm you.

563
01:00:03,745 --> 01:00:06,623
- Drink it.
- I'm so ashamed, Father.

564
01:00:06,748 --> 01:00:08,666
I may have done wrong...

565
01:00:08,792 --> 01:00:11,878
but all I want now
is a little happiness.

566
01:00:12,003 --> 01:00:14,589
Where I was born,
we had a nice home.

567
01:00:14,714 --> 01:00:16,800
We lost everything in the war.

568
01:00:18,968 --> 01:00:21,304
Then I met a man...

569
01:00:21,429 --> 01:00:24,808
an officer
in the invading army.

570
01:00:24,974 --> 01:00:28,019
He seemed
more human than the rest.

571
01:00:28,144 --> 01:00:30,897
He was young, always gay.

572
01:00:32,565 --> 01:00:35,318
I was trapped,
like all the rest.

573
01:00:37,320 --> 01:00:41,074
I - I have sinned,
but I've paid.

574
01:00:41,199 --> 01:00:43,660
You - You're a sensitive...

575
01:00:43,785 --> 01:00:46,454
experienced man.

576
01:00:46,579 --> 01:00:49,124
I am only a poor priest.

577
01:00:49,249 --> 01:00:52,961
But I can be frank with you.
I couldn't with Antonio.

578
01:00:55,213 --> 01:00:57,966
But you are the one man
who can give me comfort.

579
01:00:58,091 --> 01:01:01,219
I am no more than the parish priest
of a little community of fishermen.

580
01:01:01,344 --> 01:01:04,639
- But your human qualities I can see -
- I am a priest!

581
01:01:04,764 --> 01:01:08,852
And I can only assist you
during confession or through prayer.

582
01:01:11,688 --> 01:01:13,606
You - You -

583
01:01:15,692 --> 01:01:18,194
Your God won't help!

584
01:01:18,319 --> 01:01:19,821
You -

585
01:01:21,197 --> 01:01:23,741
Say anything you want.
All I can have for you...

586
01:01:23,867 --> 01:01:25,827
is a deep feeling of pity.

587
01:01:25,952 --> 01:01:27,996
May the Lord guide you.

588
01:01:28,121 --> 01:01:30,957
Compose yourself.
Meditate.

589
01:01:31,082 --> 01:01:32,584
Think.

590
01:01:55,231 --> 01:01:57,233
- You're home already.
- Yes.

591
01:01:57,400 --> 01:02:00,445
- I didn't expect you. Why are you so early?
- Where you been?

592
01:02:00,570 --> 01:02:03,323
Oh, I took a walk.

593
01:02:03,448 --> 01:02:06,326
I passed by the church.
Oh, what's that?

594
01:02:06,451 --> 01:02:08,328
<i>I bought it.
Un iuretto.</i>

595
01:02:08,453 --> 01:02:10,371
[Laughs] A ferret.

596
01:02:10,497 --> 01:02:13,291
[ Laughing ]
How much did you pay for it?

597
01:02:13,416 --> 01:02:16,628
[ Italian ]
Tomorrow begins tuna fishing.

598
01:02:16,753 --> 01:02:20,340
- And these?
- Gaffe. To catch fish.

599
01:02:20,465 --> 01:02:22,717
<i>What did you buy
this little animal for?</i>

600
01:02:22,842 --> 01:02:24,761
To catch wild rabbits.

601
01:02:24,886 --> 01:02:26,596
Rabbits? How?

602
01:02:26,763 --> 01:02:28,556
Do you want to see?

603
01:02:30,892 --> 01:02:32,143
Look.

604
01:02:32,268 --> 01:02:34,604
